## What Gets Constituted

### Consumer Products
Every manufactured item carries:
- What it is, what it does, what it is not
- Materials, components, origin
- Maintenance requirements, safety constraints
- Compatibility and interaction protocols
- End of life / recyclability data

AI agents shopping, recommending, or managing inventory 
instantly understand every product without external lookup.

### Industrial Equipment and Machinery
Every machine carries:
- Operating parameters and safety constraints
- Maintenance schedule and service history pointer
- Permitted operations and prohibited interactions
- Calibration state and last certification date
- Emergency procedures

A technician's AI assistant scans any machine and instantly 
knows everything about it. No manual lookup. No paper documentation.

### Infrastructure
Bridges, pipes, cables, structures carry:
- Load ratings and current stress state
- Material composition and age
- Inspection history pointers
- Permitted and prohibited loads/interactions
- Emergency contact and shutdown procedures

AI-assisted infrastructure inspection becomes possible without 
pre-loaded databases — the infrastructure introduces itself.

### Vehicles
Every vehicle carries its full constitutional payload:
- VIN-linked specification
- Service history pointer
- Current fault state
- Permitted modifications and prohibited interactions
- Emergency procedures

Workshop AI agents scan a vehicle on arrival and have complete 
context before the technician touches it. No manual rego lookup. 
No system query. The vehicle introduced itself.

### Medical Devices and Pharmaceuticals
- Device capabilities and contraindications
- Drug interactions and dosing constraints
- Patient-specific configuration pointers
- Regulatory approval status
- Expiry and storage requirements

AI-assisted medical care with full constitutional context 
from every device and medication in the environment.

### Buildings and Spaces
- Structural specifications and load ratings
- Safety systems and emergency procedures
- Access permissions and restrictions
- Environmental specifications (power, HVAC, network)
- Occupancy limits and usage constraints

AI agents operating in physical spaces understand their 
environment from the environment itself — not from 
pre-loaded building management data.

